For the capital of Eritrea, see [Asmara](/Asmara). For the city in Russia, see [Samara](/Samara). For the city in Iraq, see [Samarra](/Samarra). For the city in Ethiopia, see [Semera](/Semera). For a geographic region in the Middle East, see [Samaria](/Samaria).

## Smara

**Smara** (also romanized as Semara, [Arabic](/Arabic_language): السمارة, Hassaniyya: [&#91;(ə)s.smaːra&#93;](/Help:IPA) [ⓘ](/File:LL-Q56231_(mey)-Tidjani_Saleh-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A9.wav); [Spanish](/Spanish_language): Esmara) is a city situated within the [Moroccan](/Morocco)-occupied portion of [Western Sahara](/Western_Sahara). According to the [2014 Moroccan census](/2014_Moroccan_census), it registered a population of 57,035 individuals, a figure that undoubtedly shifts with the sands of time and political currents. &#91;1&#93; The city's connectivity to the wider world, or what passes for it in this region, is facilitated by [Smara Airport](/Smara_Airport) and a local bus station, offering routes for those brave or desperate enough to traverse the desert.

